    "narrative": "For Ghost Ride the WHIP, today\u2019s board is headlined by **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **Seiya Suzuki** (71.48), who represent our clearest paths to production. **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive 14% boost due to a favorable platoon matchup and a high-leverage spot in the two-hole, while **Seiya Suzuki** draws a 4.72 xERA starter and receives a subtle efficiency nudge from the opponent\u2019s slow delivery, which aids his potential for stolen bases\u2014our scarcest category. **Austin Riley** (67.79) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (67.69) also present as elite starts, with both leveraging friendly ballpark conditions to stay firmly in the 60+ range despite varying pitcher skill levels.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the ledger was the benching of **Cole Young** (44.59), who remains on the bubble for active play. While **Cole Young** projects as a reasonable MI option against a sub-4.00 xERA arm, he was squeezed out by the sheer efficiency of **Travis Bazzana** (55.81) and **Jose Caballero** (58.12). **Jose Caballero** carries inherent risk due to the platoon disadvantage, but his base projection and current park factor outweighed the stability of **Cole Young**. We are monitoring the status of **Corbin Carroll** (61.41) closely; while he remains a recommended start, his score is tempered by an elite hold pitcher and a negative platoon split, though his speed remains essential. With **Giancarlo Stanton** and **Max Muncy** sidelined on the IL, we continue to rely on the depth of our platoon-heavy roster to sustain our Roto categories.",
